As of the census<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were 198 people, 71 households, and 53 families living in the CDP.  There were 94 housing units.  The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census#2010 census|racial makeup]] of the CDP was 100% Native American.

Of the 67 households 37.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 9% were married couples living together, 40.3% had a female householder with no husband present, 13.4% had a male householder with no wife present, and 37.3% were non-families. 32.8% of households were one person and 7.5% were one person aged 65 or older.  The average household size was 2.81 and the average family size was 3.48.

The age distribution was 34.1% under the age of 19, 16.5% from 20 to 34, 17.3% from 35 to 49, 23.4% from 50 to 64, and 8.9% 65 or older.  The median age was 33.0 years. The population was evenly split with 50% females and 50% males.<ref name="GR2" /> The CDP saw a population growth of 0.25% between 2010 and 2015, when it reached 191 people.<ref name=AZL />

As of July 2016, the average home value was $94,565. The average household income was $41,044, with a per capita income of $11,407.<ref name=AZL />

